---
layout: base.njk
title: "The Journal"
description: "Thoughtful, practical writing advice from The Quiet Pen — on wedding vows, speeches, toasts, and finding the words for life's biggest moments."
eleventyExcludeFromCollections: true
---
{% from "icons.njk" import featherIllustration %}

<section class="page-hero">
  <div class="container">
    <p class="breadcrumb"><a href="/">Home</a> / Journal</p>
    <div class="section-header reveal">
      <span class="eyebrow">The Journal</span>
      <h1>Thoughtful answers, not finished speeches.</h1>
      <p class="lede">
        We'd rather teach you something useful than hand you a script to copy. Here's what we've
        learned about writing for the moments that matter most.
      </p>
    </div>
  </div>
</section>

<section class="section-tight">
  <div class="container">
    <div class="grid grid-3">
      {% for post in collections.blogPosts %}
      <div class="blog-card reveal reveal-delay-{{ loop.index0 % 4 + 1 }}">
        <a class="blog-card-image" href="{{ post.url }}" aria-hidden="true" tabindex="-1">
          {{ featherIllustration() }}
        </a>
        <span class="blog-meta">{{ post.data.category | default("Journal") }} &middot; {{ post.data.readTime }}</span>
        <h3><a href="{{ post.url }}">{{ post.data.title }}</a></h3>
        <p class="text-muted">{{ post.data.description }}</p>
      </div>
      {% endfor %}
    </div>
  </div>
</section>

<section class="section section-alt">
  <div class="container-narrow text-center reveal">
    <span class="eyebrow" style="justify-content:center;">Want More Than an Article?</span>
    <h2>Some things are easier with a guide, or a second pair of eyes.</h2>
    <div class="cluster" style="justify-content:center; margin-top: var(--space-md);">
      <a class="btn btn-primary" href="/workbook/">Browse the Workbook</a>
      <a class="btn btn-secondary" href="/services/">Explore Writing Services</a>
    </div>
  </div>
</section>
